&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;GW&amp;amp;K Investment Management seeks an experienced Channel Marketing Manager to lead the development and execution of integrated marketing campaigns, including driving new content development, coordinating webinars/events and managing partner materials submissions. This individual will directly drive the growth and success of key distribution channels, including RIAs, broker-dealers, and wirehouses, by facilitating engagement and supporting business objectives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will be responsible for increasing advisor engagement and accomplishing channel objectives through multi-channel &amp;nbsp;marketing initiatives. Success in this position will have a measurable impact on advancing business priorities in collaboration with the broader marketing team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Channel Marketing Manager will work closely with National Accounts and Sales teams to align marketing programs with distribution priorities, while serving as the primary liaison between advisory distribution channels and GW&amp;amp;K’s marketing organization.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will play a key part in developing and evolving GW&amp;amp;K’s advisory channel marketing efforts. Responsibilities include expanding digital engagement, enhancing advisor-facing campaigns, and building GW&amp;amp;K’s channel function as the business continues to grow.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the planning and execution of integrated marketing campaigns aligned to channel priorities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define channel-specific marketing approaches, including target audiences, messaging, and campaign strategies, in collaboration with Marketing and Business Development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with digital, social, creative and content teams to deliver cohesive, cross-channel campaigns&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with National Accounts and Sales to support platform initiatives, partner campaigns, and advisor outreach&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the primary point of contact for advisory channel marketing needs, ensuring alignment across stakeholders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support and enhance sales enablement efforts, including content development, effective use of tools such as Seismic and LinkedIn as well as ensuring the delivery of campaign intelligence to support sales efforts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor trends across the U.S. wealth channel landscape and apply insights to refine channel marketing efforts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage campaign execution, including timelines, deliverables, and cross-functional coordination&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee compliance submission and approval processes for marketing materials&amp;nbsp; at sponsor firms’ compliance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track and analyze campaign performance, providing relevant insights and recommendations to improve effectiveness&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to the development of reporting systems that track progress against engagement and business objectives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of developing and executing integrated, multi-channel marketing strategies within channels (RIA, broker-dealer, wirehouse)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Marketing, Communications, or a related field. Equivalent professional experience is also acceptable.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7–10+ years of experience in investment management marketing or distribution. Experience with separately managed account distribution is preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to manage campaigns, priorities, and stakeholders in fast-paced settings. Highly organized and attentive to detail.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience partnering with Sales and National Accounts to support distribution initiatives, advisor engagement, and growth objectives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt
